item.dc:creator: @LilXCj LilXCj
item.description:
@LilXCj wrote:

[quote=“zyle1992, post:46, topic:382607”][quote author=Anc13nts253 link=topic=478401.msg3505362#msg3505362 date=1298105276]

Since when could you have a username with < 4 characters?

Since when the days were around when they wern’t all taken up.

Have they used 15,885,972,449,706,303 usernames? I doubt it.

(Math: 63 possible characters(Uppercase, Lowercase, digits, _) 12 char max, 4 char min, 63 + 63^2 + … + 63^8 + 63^9)

Uppercase & lowercase doesn’t matter. They would still be counted as the same.

There is 37 Different keys you can use, 0-9 & A-Z nothing can Contain Symbols, but yes. There is still a few 3 letter names left, just hard to find them sometimes. I grabbed my 3 letter name when they reset a lot of accounts.
[/quote]

I guess since they added the nickname system, they might have allowed < 4 letter names.

And I forgot, things were only capitalised if the character was directly after a space/underscore[/quote]

There wasn’t a limit to number of characters in names in 2001. Hence < 3 character names.
